---
description: Avoid Playwright visual inspection on auth-protected routes without an active session
alwaysApply: true
---

# Auth-Aware Visual Verification

- This project uses Clerk auth. Routes that require sign-in, including trading terminal, dashboard, room, profile, and join flows, are auth-blocked for fresh agent Playwright sessions.
- Do not repeatedly try Playwright visual inspection for authenticated pages unless the user explicitly provides a signed-in browser/session path or asks to debug auth.
- Public routes such as the home page can still be inspected with Playwright when useful.
- For protected UI work, verify with code review, linting, typecheck, and component-level reasoning. In the final response, clearly state that live visual inspection of protected routes was skipped because authentication blocks the agent session.
- If visual verification is essential, ask the user to either inspect it in their signed-in browser or provide a route/session setup that the agent can access.
